rview of the attack on poverty, Martin Rein, S.M. Miller, and Harris Chaiklin have contributed short papers on the American experience, and B.W. Lappin has presented the problem from the Canadian point of view. Professor Schlesinger has outlined a Canadian profile of poverty, together with the various anti-poverty programs suggested by the Canadian government, since these are less well known and documented than the American counterparts. In addition there is an appendix of articles on poverty found in popular periodicals, and a list of bibliographies on poverty or related topics. Teachers, students, and professionals in the various disciplines named above will find this bibliography valuable, and it will be of interest too to researchers, government officials, and program planners concerned with the War on Poverty.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aPoorzCanadavBibliography. 0aPoorzUnited StatesvBibliography. 0aPovertyvBibliography. 7aREFERENCE / Bibliographies & Indexes.2bisacsh1 aChaiklin, Harris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLappin, B. W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, S. Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRein, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchlesinger, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148758383540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487583835423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487583835.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_E